AN ACT making an appropriation to the Nevada Test Site
Historical Foundation for exhibits and improvements at
the National Atomic Testing Museum; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State
2 General Fund to the Nevada Test Site Historical Foundation the sum
3 of $2,500,000 for exhibits and improvements at the National Atomic
4 Testing Museum in Las Vegas, Nevada.
5 2. Upon acceptance of the money appropriated by subsection 1,
6 the Foundation agrees to:
7 (a) Prepare and transmit a report to the Interim Finance
8 Committee on or before December 18, 2026, that describes each
9 expenditure made from the money appropriated by subsection 1
10 from the date on which the money was received by the Foundation
11 through December 1, 2026;
12 (b) Prepare and transmit a final report to the Interim Finance
13 Committee on or before September 17, 2027, that describes each
14 expenditure made from the money appropriated by subsection 1
15 from the date on which the money was received by the Foundation
16 through June 30, 2027; and
